Package: edaphos
Title: Disruptive Algorithms for Digital Soil Mapping
Version: 3.10.0
Authors@R:
    person("Hugo", "Rodrigues", , "rodrigues.machado.hugo@gmail.com",
           role = c("aut", "cre"),
           comment = c(ORCID = "0000-0002-8070-8126"))
Description: Frontier algorithms for Digital Soil Mapping organised
    around ten research pillars: Causal AI with backdoor-adjusted
    effect estimation on pedogenetic Directed Acyclic Graphs and
    LLM-driven Knowledge Graphs; Physics-Informed Machine Learning
    via a parametric pedogenetic Ordinary Differential Equation and
    a differentiable Neural ODE; 4D Pedometry with stacked
    Convolutional Long Short-Term Memory networks plus an Ensemble
    Kalman Filter for sequential assimilation; Foundation Models
    via SimCLR / MoCo contrastive pre-training on raster patches;
    Active Learning with hybrid uncertainty + diversity batch
    policies and physics-informed gates; Quantum Machine Learning
    via a pure-R ZZFeatureMap state-vector simulator and quantum
    kernel ridge regression; Bayesian Hierarchical Spatial models
    with a profile-MLE Gibbs sampler (RcppArmadillo backend); Neural
    Operators (DeepONet and Fourier Neural Operator) over depth
    function space; Diffusion Models (DDPM) for soil-property maps;
    and Graph Attention Networks on k-NN co-location graphs of
    profiles. Six v3.0.0 cross-pillar bridges and a unified
    edaphos_posterior calibration class let every method be scored
    with the same diagnostics. A synthesised Cerrado dataset is
    bundled so every vignette runs offline.
